sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates a Read Replica of DB Instance.

Inputs:

  • Region - Region of the RDS resource.
  • DB Instance Read Replica Identifier - The DB instance identifier of the Read Replica. This identifier is the unique key that identifies a DB instance. This parameter is stored as a lowercase string.
  • Source DB Instance Identifier - The identifier of the DB instance that will act as the source for the Read Replica. Each DB instance can have up to five Read Replicas.

Outputs:

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid database identifier: "Provided DB identifier".
  • DB instance is not in the available state
  • Missing Authentication Token.

(For information about the errors that are common to all actions, see Common Errors).

To use this action, a corresponding Amazon RDS credential must be created and associated with the Amazon RDS Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More
